                <!--   Power Supply to Motherboard   -->
                <div class="mainContainers" id="mC2">
                    <h1>Components 1-5</h1>

                    <a id='com4'><h2>Power Supply & Case</h2></a>
                    <h3>Power Supply</h3>
                    <p> Converts AC from the wall outlet to DC to give a continuous source of power to the computer.</p>
                    <h3>Case</h3>
                    <p> Hold the components of the computer and contains the motherboard.</p>
                    <a id='com5'><h2>Hard Drive</h2></a>
                    <p> Permanent and long-term storage holding data currently not in use.</p>
                    <a id='com6'>
                        <h2>Random Access Memory</h2>
                    </a>
                        <p> Non-permanent and short-term storage for quickly accessing small amounts of data that are currently in use.</p>
                        <a id='com7'>
                            <h2>Central Processing Unit</h2>
                        </a>
                            <p> Recieves input instructions, processes said instructions, then performs the given task. The CPU is meant to do calculations and let the other components communicate.</p>
                            <a id='com8'>
                                <h2>Motherboard</h2>
                            </a>
                                <p> Connects all the pieces of the computer together so that the parts can communicate. Every physical component is connected to the motherboard, whether directly or through cables.</p>
                </div>
